---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';

const updated = 'July 1, 2026';
const email = 'contact@verapeakdigital.com';
---

<Base
  title="Privacy Policy | Verapeak Digital"
  description="How Verapeak Digital collects, uses, stores, and protects your information — including data from our website, analytics, and advertising services."
>
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="eyebrow">Legal</span>
      <h1>Privacy <span class="text-grad">Policy</span></h1>
      <p class="lead">
        This policy explains what information we collect, how we use and store it, and the
        choices you have. We keep it plain-English on purpose — transparency is our whole thing.
      </p>
      <p class="updated">Last updated: {updated}</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="legal-section">
    <div class="container legal">
      <h2>Who we are</h2>
      <p>
        Verapeak Digital ("Verapeak," "we," "us," or "our") is a digital marketing agency based in
        Knoxville, Tennessee, serving clients nationwide. This policy applies to
        <a href="https://verapeakdigital.com">verapeakdigital.com</a> and the reporting tools we
        operate for our clients. If you have questions, contact us at
        <a href={`mailto:${email}`}>{email}</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>Information we collect</h2>
      <h3>Information you give us</h3>
      <p>
        When you submit a form or contact us, we collect the details you provide — typically your
        name, email address, phone number, company, and any message, budget, or service interest
        you include. We use this to respond to your inquiry and provide the services you request.
      </p>
      <h3>Information collected automatically</h3>
      <p>
        When you visit our site, we and our analytics providers automatically collect standard
        technical and usage information, such as your device and browser type, approximate
        location (derived from IP address), pages viewed, links clicked, referring website, and
        UTM campaign parameters. We use both Google Analytics 4 and our own first-party
        measurement (Verapeak Insights) to understand site performance and to attribute leads to
        the marketing channel they came from.
      </p>
      <h3>Cookies and similar technologies</h3>
      <p>
        We use cookies and similar technologies for essential site functionality, analytics, and
        measuring advertising performance. You can control non-essential cookies through the
        consent banner shown on our site and through your browser settings. Disabling some cookies
        may affect how the site works.
      </p>

      <h2>How we use your information</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>To respond to inquiries and provide our marketing services;</li>
        <li>To operate, secure, maintain, and improve our website and tools;</li>
        <li>To measure website performance and attribute leads to marketing channels;</li>
        <li>To measure and improve the performance of advertising campaigns;</li>
        <li>To send service communications and, where permitted, relevant updates;</li>
        <li>To comply with legal obligations and enforce our terms.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Analytics and advertising services</h2>
      <p>
        We use third-party analytics and advertising platforms — including Google Analytics,
        Google Ads, and Meta (Facebook &amp; Instagram) — to measure performance and, for our
        clients, to report on advertising results. These providers may set their own cookies and
        process data under their own privacy policies. You can learn about Google's practices and
        opt out of Google Analytics using the tools below:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Google Privacy Policy</a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Google Analytics Opt-out Browser Add-on</a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://www.facebook.com/privacy/policy" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Meta Privacy Policy</a>
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        When we manage advertising accounts on behalf of a client, we access that client's
        Google Ads, Google Analytics, or Meta data only to provide reporting and optimization for
        that client. We do not sell this data or use it for any unrelated purpose.
      </p>

      <h2>How we store and protect your information</h2>
      <p>
        Your information is stored on reputable cloud infrastructure and access is restricted to
        authorized personnel who need it to do their work. Sensitive credentials and access tokens
        are encrypted, and client reporting data is isolated so that each client can only access
        their own information. While no method of transmission or storage is 100% secure, we take
        reasonable technical and organizational measures to protect your data.
      </p>

      <h2>How long we keep it</h2>
      <p>
        We retain personal information only for as long as needed to fulfill the purposes described
        here, to comply with our legal obligations, resolve disputes, and enforce our agreements.
        When it is no longer needed, we delete or anonymize it.
      </p>

      <h2>How we share information</h2>
      <p>
        We do not sell your personal information. We share it only with service providers who help
        us operate our business (for example, analytics, advertising, hosting, and form/email
        providers), when required by law, or to protect our rights. These providers are permitted
        to use your information only to perform services for us.
      </p>

      <h2>Your choices and rights</h2>
      <p>
        Depending on where you live, you may have the right to access, correct, delete, or restrict
        the use of your personal information, and to opt out of certain processing. To make a
        request, email us at <a href={`mailto:${email}`}>{email}</a> and we will respond in
        accordance with applicable law.
      </p>

      <h2>Third-party links</h2>
      <p>
        Our site may link to third-party websites we do not control. This policy does not apply to
        those sites, and we encourage you to review their privacy policies.
      </p>

      <h2>Children's privacy</h2>
      <p>
        Our website and services are intended for businesses and are not directed to children
        under 13, and we do not knowingly collect personal information from them.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this policy from time to time. When we do, we will revise the "Last updated"
        date above. Material changes will be reflected on this page.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact us</h2>
      <p>
        Verapeak Digital<br />
        Knoxville, TN · Serving the United States<br />
        Email: <a href={`mailto:${email}`}>{email}</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  .updated {
    margin-top: 14px;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--muted, #6b7f7c);
  }
  .legal-section {
    padding-bottom: 96px;
  }
  .legal {
    max-width: 760px;
  }
  .legal h2 {
    margin-top: 44px;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    line-height: 1.2;
  }
  .legal h3 {
    margin-top: 24px;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
  }
  .legal p,
  .legal li {
    color: #3f524f;
    line-height: 1.7;
    font-size: 1.02rem;
  }
  .legal p {
    margin-bottom: 14px;
  }
  .legal ul {
    margin: 0 0 14px 1.1rem;
    display: grid;
    gap: 6px;
  }
  .legal a {
    color: var(--brand, #0f766e);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }
  .legal a:hover {
    color: var(--mint, #0d9488);
  }
</style>
